<html xmlns:wicket="http://wicket.apache.org">
<wicket:extend>
	
	<div class="content">
	<div class="account_management_text">Product Payment</div>
	<br />
	<div style="color:#FF0000"><span wicket:id="feedback">feedback messages will be
	put here</span></div>
	<span style="font-weight:bold">Payment <span wicket:id="amountLbl"></span></span><br/>
	<br/>
	<div style="padding-left:100px;font-size:11px">
		<div wicket:id="cardList"> 
			<form wicket:id="cardForm">
			<span wicket:id="nameLbl"></span>&nbsp;
			<span wicket:id="maskedNumberLbl"></span>&nbsp;
			<input type="submit" value="Purchase with this card"/>			
			</form>
		</div>
	</div>
	<br/>
<hr>
<br/>
	<div class="products_form">
	
	<div style="float: left; width: 350px">

	<form wicket:id="paymentForm">

	<div wicket:id="payments">
	<h3 style="text-align:center">Credit Card Information</h3>
	<ul class="pay-form">
		<li>
		<div class="form-left-pay">Card Holder Name:</div>
		<div><input wicket:id="cardHolderName"
			class="form-left-input-pay" type="text" maxlength="32" size="30" /></div>
		</li>

		<li>
		<div class="form-left-pay">Credit Card Number:</div>
		<div><input wicket:id="creditCardNo" class="form-left-input-pay"
			type="text" maxlength="32" size="30" /></div>
		</li>

		<li>
		<div class="form-left-pay">Expiry(MM/YYYY):</div>
		<div><input wicket:id="cardExpiryDate"
			class="form-left-input-pay" type="text" maxlength="32" size="30" />
		</div>
		</li>

		<li>
		<div class="form-left-pay">CVV:</div>
		<div><input wicket:id="cvv" class="form-left-input-pay"
			type="text" maxlength="32" size="30" /></div>
		</li>

	</ul>

	<div class="purchase_btn" style="margin-left: 150px;"><input type="submit"
		class="btn" value="" /></div>
	</div>
	</form>

	<div
		style="text-align: center; width: 100%; background-color: #FFFFCC; font-weight: bold">
	</div>
	</div>
	<div style="font-size:11px">
	<span style="font-weight:bold">What happens if we upgrade, downgrade, or cancel in the middle of a billing cycle?</span><br/><br/>  
	If you upgrade or downgrade you'll be charged the new rate for your new plan starting on your next billing cycle. 
	If you cancel you'll be cancelled immediately and you won't be charged again.<br/><br/>
	<span style="font-weight:bold">We accept</span><br/> 
	<img src="images/cards.jpg"/><br/>
	Visa, Mastercard, and American Express. We don't accept PayPal, checks or POs, sorry.
	</div>
	<div class="clear"></div>
	</div>
	</div>
</wicket:extend>

</html>
